Asaba, – Elections retuning officer, for Aniocha/Oshimili Federal Constituency of Delta,  Prof. Kenneth Ibe on Monday in Asaba. The House of Representatives Minority Leader, Mr Ndudi Elumelu of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), has been defeated by the Labour Party (LP) candidate, Mr Ngozi Okolie, in Aniocha/Oshimili Federal Constituency of Delta. Elumelu pooled a total of 33,456 votes, while the LP candidate polled a total of 53,879 votes to emerge winner as announced by the Independent National Electoral Commisisom, Returning Officer, Prof. Kenneth Ibe, on Monday in Asaba. Aniocha-Oshimili,   Delta (Press Release)       -     Discrepancies in vote tally and emerging proofs that unaccredited persons may have voted in the inconclusive primary election to pick a flag bearer in the Aniocha-Oshimili federal constituency for the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) led to the stalemate. The primary was… In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Group under the auspices of National Youths Vanguard for Democracy (NYVD) has called on the People’s Democratic Party, (PDP) not to succumb to the pressure to substitute Elumelu's name with that of Mrs. Mrakpor. The group which recalled that a transparent primary election… In "News" By Festus Ahon, Asaba Abuja - Minority Leader of the Federal House of Representatives and member representing Aniocha/Oshimili Federal Constituency, Mr. Ndudi Elumelu has appointed 125 youths and women drawn from across the constituency as his political aides. Presenting the appointment letters to the selected women and youths at his… In "Top Stories"